definition.value: Sexual attraction toward the elderly.
Sexual attraction to adults.
Primary or exclusive sexual attraction to prepubescent and pubescent children by an adult.
Any of various disorders primarily characterized by pedohebephilia.
The primary sexual attraction of adults to very young children (defined by various studies as 0–4).
Adult sexual attraction primarily towards pubescent children.

Note that this term and others like it are often to deflect more stigmatizing terms like "pedophillia" and may be used to argue in some cases that such attractions are more normal and therefore not as bad as "real" pedophillia.
Primary adult sexual attraction towards late pubescent or postpubescent adolescents.
L. Pierce Clark (1914) defined ephebophilia as "lovers of youths" from ages "14-21".

Note that this term and others like it are often to deflect more stigmatizing terms like "pedophillia" and may be used to argue in some cases that such attractions are more normal and therefore not as bad as "real" pedophillia.
A sexual preference for middle-aged adults.
Sexual behavior involving young adolescents or children in a sense that may be normative in the given society, such as pederasty was in ancient Greece.
Homosexual relations in which partners are of different ages, usually in which one partner is an adolescent and the other is an adult, although this is not always the case.
Homosexual relations in which each partner plays a different gender role (exemplified, for instance, in stereotypical North American lesbian butch/femme relationships).
Homosexual relations in which age bears no relevance and both partners play the same socially-accepted sex role as heterosexual persons of their own sex.

definition.value: Erotic love, sexually expressed or chaste, between a man and an adolescent boy.
Pederasty in ancient Greece was a socially acknowledged romantic relationship between an adult male (the erastes) and a younger male (the eromenos) usually in his teens.

Athenian pederasty entailed a formal bond between an adult man and an adolescent boy outside his immediate family, consisting of loving and often sexual relations. As an erotic and educational custom it was initially employed by the upper class as a means of teaching the young and conveying to them important cultural values, such as bravery and restraint.
Cretan pederasty was an archaic form of pederasty that involved the ritual kidnapping (harpagmos) of a noble boy by an adult male of the aristocratic class, with the consent of the boy's father.
A BDSM sexual activity involving the application of pain or pressure to a vulva or vagina, typically in the context of sadomasochism.

A slang term in Afghanistan for a wide variety of activities involving sexual relations between older men and younger adolescent men, or boys. The practitioner is commonly called bacha baz (meaning "boy play" in Dari) or simply bach. It may include to some extent sexual slavery and child prostitution. Bacha bāzī is currently reported in various parts of Afghanistan. Force and coercion are common, and security officials state they are unable to end such practices because many of the men involved in bacha bazi-related activities are powerful and well-armed warlords.

A Filipino identity which is considered nonnormative in terms of gender and/or sexuality. Depending on the context, such a person may also consider themselves to be gay, transgender, bisexual, or otherwise part of a cultural gender identity exclusive to the Philippines. However, the term is almost always applied to persons assigned male at birth.
The argot utilized by the baklâ is called swardspeak, sometimes called gayspeak.
The baklâ identity precedes colonization of the Philippines. Such persons were often held in high regard, being spiritual leaders sometimes called babaylan and katalonan.
A woman who is accorded the status of a man without disrupting the patriarchal status quo.
Women who take a vow of chastity and wear male clothing in order to live as men in patriarchal Balkan society.
Women who take a vow of chastity and wear male clothing in order to live as men in patriarchal northern Albanian society.
Women who take a vow of chastity and wear male clothing in order to live as men in patriarchal Montenegrin society.
Persons who cross-dress for the purposes of performance.
Persons who cross-dress for cultural reasons or purposes.
Persons who cross-dress for the purposes of disguise.
Persons who cross-dress during wartime under various circumstances and for various motives.

A grouping of humans based on shared physical or social qualities into categories generally viewed as distinct by society. The term was first used to refer to speakers of a common language and then to denote national affiliations. By the 17th century the term began to refer to physical (phenotypical) traits. Modern scholarship regards race as a social construct, an identity which is assigned based on rules made by society. While partially based on physical similarities within groups, race does not have an inherent physical or biological meaning.

Race is a characteristic of an individual defined by some culturally-defined combination of heritable phenotypic characteristics, geographic ancestry, physical appearance, ethnicity, and social status.
Coitus by circumstance or location.
Sexual intercourse in water or underwater.
Types of coitus in relation to the given partners' marital status.
Sexual intercourse which takes place on horseback or, rarely, sexual intercourse in which one partner acts out the role of a horse.

An erotic or relational context is entirely defined by the people involved and by their mood and interests at the time of play. It ranges from the simple imitation of a vocal "whinnying" of a horse to the barking, panting or playful nudging of a puppy, or playful behaviour of a kitten, to crawling around on all fours and being fed, or petted, by hand. To the greater extremes of dressing up as a pony in modified horse tack, masks, prosthetics and temporary bondage based body modification (such as binding the forearms to the upperarms and/or the calves to the thighs).
Role play in which at least one of the participants dresses to resemble and assumes the mannerisms and character of an equine animal.
Sexual role play in which one of the participants acts out canine mannerisms and behaviors, which are sometimes associated with leather culture.

Sexual role play in which a person dresses to resemble and assumes the mannerisms and character of a kitten or cat, a characteristic of which is that it keeps some independence and, as part of the fantasy, might retaliate against the partner trying to tame/train them.
The introduction of polymeric organic silicon based material via injection.
Vaginal intercourse in which the vaginal partner assumes a knee-chest position and the penile partner kneels behind them, entering the vagina from the rear.
Any of various sex positions in which the penile partner enters the vagina from the rear.
Extramarital coitus that is considered objectionable on social, religious, moral, or legal grounds.
The state of voluntarily being unmarried, sexually abstinent, or both, usually for religious reasons.
Not engaging in sexual intercourse or other activities by one's own will.
Not engaging in sexual intercourse or other activities against one's own volition.
The state of refraining from premarital and extramarital sex, for primarily religious and/or cultural reasons.

Note that "chastity" may also refer to a form of erotic sexual denial practiced in BDSM communities, wherein a person (usually the submissive) is denied sexual stimulation, sometimes by means of an external device (such as a chastity belt or cock cage).
A type of prosthetic created for the purpose of simulating an intact human hymen.
Refraining from sexual intercourse in the postpartum period.

Primarily sexual frustration experienced by those who label themselves as "incels" (involuntary celibates). Broadly, any person who wants to be sexually active, but is held back by social rules and laws.

At least seven mass murders, resulting in a total of 46 deaths, have been committed since 2014 by men who have either self-identified as incels or who had mentioned incel-related names and writings in their private writings or Internet postings. Incel communities have been criticized by researchers and the media for being misogynistic, encouraging violence, spreading extremist views, and radicalizing their members.
A shift, alteration, modification, or evolution of human behavior and culture, which over time, results in measurable consequences on societal values and norms.

A social movement is a type of group action. There is no single consensus definition of a social movement. They are large, sometimes informal, groupings of individuals or organizations which focus on specific political or social issues. In other words, they carry out, resist, or undo a social change. They provide a way of social change from the bottom within nations.
A type of movement or political ideology which seeks to increase the acceptability of individual characteristics of one's identity (such as race, ethnic group, gender, and sexual orientation).
